VARICELLA, SCHOOL CHILDREN - USA (NORTH CAROLINA) (02)
******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Thu 7 Dec 2006
From: Prof. Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: The GIDEON Database, Thu 7 Dec 2006 [edited]
<http://www.GideonOnline.com>

ProMED-mail reminds us that Americans continue to die of Varicella
[see: ProMED-mail post entitled "Varicella, school children - USA
(NC) 20061206.3442]. In fact, varicella is the most common fatal
'childhood disease' in the USA
(<http://exhibit.gideononline.com/varicella-usa.jpg>).
Varicella ranks 4th among all vaccine-preventable deaths
(<http://exhibit.gideononline.com/vaccines-usa.jpg>).
--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
[ProMED-mail thanks Steve Berger for providing this interesting
information extracted from the Gideon database. - Mod.CP]
